# ============================================
# C++ PROJECT EXECUTABLES (NO EXTENSION)
# ============================================

# 🎯 UNIVERSAL SOLUTION: Ignore ALL executables (files without extensions)
# This works for ANY filename you create!
# 
# How it works:
# 1. Ignore all files in C++ folders
# 2. But keep files with extensions (.cpp, .md, .txt, etc.)
# 3. But keep directories
#
# This means:
# ✅ 01-Functions.cpp    → Tracked (has .cpp extension)
# ❌ 01-Functions        → Ignored (no extension = executable)
# ✅ 02-Functions.cpp    → Tracked (has .cpp extension)
# ❌ 02-Functions        → Ignored (no extension = executable)
# ✅ myProgram.cpp       → Tracked (has .cpp extension)
# ❌ myProgram           → Ignored (no extension = executable)
# ✅ README.md           → Tracked (has .md extension)
# ✅ folder/             → Tracked (is a directory)

# Step 1: Ignore everything in C++ folders
C++/**/*

# Step 2: But DON'T ignore files with ANY extension
!C++/**/*.*

# Step 3: But DON'T ignore directories (so we can traverse them)
!C++/**/

# Step 4: But DO ignore common executable extensions (just in case)
C++/**/*.out
C++/**/*.exe
C++/**/*.app

# 🔥 RESULT: This pattern ignores ALL executables regardless of name!
# Works for: 01-Functions, 02-Functions, myCode, test, anything!
# No need to manually add each executable name! 🎉

